  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PEOPLE EU Volunteers capacity stengthening project - Caritas Sierra Leone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of the wider EU Aid Volunteers funded PEOPLE project, working with 10 organisations across Africa. The main purpose of the PEOPLE project is to enable local and national organisations such as the National Commission of Justice, Peace and Caritas of Liberia to improve the quality and effectiveness of their humanitarian preparedness and response capacity, and their volunteer management systems. This will be done through a process of capacity self-assessment and capacity strengthening action planning, Training of Trainers and cascading of learning on key emergency response and volunteer topics, and peer learning between the 10 organisations involved in the programme. CAFOD staff will provide support throughout this process.

The project objectives are to:
1. Strengthen humanitarian preparedness and response capacity of NCJPC Liberia to design and deliver needs based humanitarian aid.
2. Strengthen volunteer management capacity of NCJPC Liberia to facilitate integration and active participation of volunteers in humanitarian action.
3. Strengthen collective dialogue, knowledge sharing, learning and peer- to-peer support between NCJPC Liberia and other partners on emergency response and volunteers.</narrative>
  </description>
